description: We used whole-genome bisulfite sequencing (WGBS) to generate unbiased DNA methylation maps of six purified B-cell subpopulations: hematopoietic progenitor cells (HPC); pre-B-II cells (preB2C); naive B cells from peripheral blood (naiBC); germinal center B cells (gcBC); memory B cells from peripheral blood (memBC) and plasma cells from bone marrow (bm-PC). WGBS was performed in 2 biological replicates from each subpopulation.
